The paper discusses a mechanism for memory disaggregation in datacenters, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses algorithms for cluster-wide memory management, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper addresses resilience mechanisms, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper discusses the use of erasure coding, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of RDMA, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
